From 75819a70032d682f77cfad84d41726f8bef72684 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 12:36:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.4a: Decompose Messages god-component into 4 focused
 components
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Breaks the 395-line Messages.jsx god-component into a thin orchestrator
(129 lines) plus four focused child components and two helpers. Absorbs
T2.2c (Messages react-query migration) — the useState+useEffect+subscribe
pattern is replaced with useQuery + a dedicated useThreadMessages hook
as part of the extraction.

New file layout:

  src/pages/Messages.jsx (orchestrator, 129 lines)
    - holds top-level state: selectedThread, showMobileConvo,
      showNewThread
    - two useQuery calls: MessageThread list and approved User list
    - realtime subscription that invalidates the thread list on any
      entity change
    - composes the four components below

  src/components/messages/ThreadList.jsx (90 lines)
    - sidebar list of conversations with unread indicators
    - pure presentation, all data from props

  src/components/messages/MessageThreadView.jsx (126 lines)
    - conversation pane: header, message list, scroll behavior
    - uses useThreadMessages hook for data + realtime
    - composer rendered via a 'composer' prop for separation of concerns

  src/components/messages/MessageComposer.jsx (140 lines)
    - textarea + attachment chips + file upload + send button
    - owns its own state (draft text, attachments, sending/uploading flags)
    - send logic unchanged from the old implementation

  src/components/messages/NewThreadModal.jsx (147 lines)
    - recipient picker, subject input, create thread mutation
    - invalidates MessageThread cache on create

  src/hooks/useThreadMessages.js (51 lines)
    - useQuery for messages scoped to a thread_id
    - realtime subscription that mutates the query cache directly
      (setQueryData) for immediate feedback without round-trip

  src/lib/messageUtils.js (36 lines)
    - pure formatting helpers: formatMessageTime,
      getOtherParticipantName, isThreadUnread

Behavior preserved exactly:
- Thread list filters to current user's participation (same semantics)
- Selecting a thread clears unread flag and scrolls to bottom
- Realtime subscription still fires on message create/update/delete
- Mobile nav (hide thread list when conversation is open, back button)
  works identically

Behavior slightly improved:
- Message cache updates optimistically via setQueryData on realtime
  events (was already inline; now explicitly scoped to the hook)
- Failed 'clear unread' is non-fatal (thread still opens; was silent
  before, now wrapped in try/catch with a comment explaining why)
- ARIA labels added to icon-only buttons (file attach, send, back,
  close, remove attachment, new thread)

Also absorbs T2.2c:
Messages.jsx now uses useQuery for its two list fetches (MessageThread
and approved Users). No more manual useState+useEffect+loadThreads.
NewThreadModal invalidates the cache on create. This matches the
pattern established in T2.2a through T2.2g.

Files:
- Changed: src/pages/Messages.jsx (395 -> 129 lines)
- Added: src/components/messages/ThreadList.jsx
- Added: src/components/messages/MessageThreadView.jsx
- Added: src/components/messages/MessageComposer.jsx
- Added: src/components/messages/NewThreadModal.jsx
- Added: src/hooks/useThreadMessages.js
- Added: src/lib/messageUtils.js

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
- Scoped lint: 0 errors, 0 warnings on all new files
- npm run build: succeeds
